# Zama FHEVM â€” Cursor Rules
# Generated from SKILL.md v1.0.0 | @fhevm/solidity v0.11.1
# Full reference: ./SKILL.md

## CRITICAL: Package

- ALWAYS use `@fhevm/solidity` â€” NEVER `fhevm-solidity` (archived June 2025)
- Install: `npm install @fhevm/solidity @zama-fhe/relayer-sdk @openzeppelin/contracts`
- Import: `import "@fhevm/solidity/lib/FHE.sol";`
- Base contract: `import "@fhevm/solidity/config/ZamaConfig.sol";` â†’ inherit `ZamaEthereumConfig`

## CRITICAL: Encrypted Types (v0.11.1)

Use ONLY these types â€” eint/ebytes are declared but have no operations:
- `euint8`, `euint16`, `euint32`, `euint64`, `euint128`, `euint160`, `euint256`
- `ebool`, `eaddress`
- ZKPoK inputs: `externalEuint8`...`externalEuint256`, `externalEbool`, `externalEaddress`

euint256 restriction: ONLY `eq`, `ne`, `and`, `or`, `xor`, `select` â€” NO arithmetic.

## CRITICAL: ACL â€” Every handle needs permissions

After every computation or storage:
```solidity
FHE.allowThis(handle);          // contract can use it
FHE.allow(handle, userAddress); // user can decrypt it
```
Missing ACL = handle permanently inaccessible.

## CRITICAL: ZKPoK Inputs

NEVER accept raw uint64 from users â€” always validate with ZKPoK:
```solidity
function deposit(externalEuint64 encryptedAmount, bytes calldata inputProof) external {
    euint64 amount = FHE.fromExternal(encryptedAmount, inputProof);
    // now safe to use `amount`
}
```

## CRITICAL: Decryption

No synchronous decrypt. Use `FHE.makePubliclyDecryptable` + relayer SDK:
```solidity
FHE.makePubliclyDecryptable(handle); // mark for off-chain decryption
// Frontend reads via: instance.publicDecrypt([handleHex])
```

## HCU Limits

- Global per tx: 20M HCU
- Sequential ops: 5M HCU max
- euint64 mul = 365K HCU, euint64 div = 715K HCU
- Keep loops short â€” silent revert on HCU overflow

## Anti-Patterns (AP-001 to AP-020)

AP-001: Wrong package (`fhevm-solidity`) â†’ use `@fhevm/solidity`
AP-002: Missing `ZamaEthereumConfig` base â†’ inherit it
AP-003: Missing `FHE.allowThis()` after store â†’ add it
AP-004: euint256 arithmetic â†’ use euint128 or lower
AP-005: `TFHE.decrypt()` sync â†’ removed in v0.5, use relayer pattern
AP-006: `FHE.div(a, encryptedB)` â†’ divisor must be plaintext
AP-007: Raw uint input without ZKPoK â†’ use `externalEuintXX` + `FHE.fromExternal()`
AP-008: Callback replay â†’ check `callbackCalled` flag, reset before external call
AP-010: HCU overflow (silent revert) â†’ stay under 5M sequential
AP-015: Missing `FHE.isAllowed()` check before decrypt â†’ add the check
AP-016: Missing reentrancy guard on decrypt callback â†’ add `nonReentrant`

